text: == Events == * The Kings of Wessex take control of Devon. * Otto I crowned Holy Roman Emperor at Aachen. * King Taejo of Goryeo defeats Hubaekje. * Prince Bei, elder brother of the Liao Dynasty emperor, is murdered by the Later Tang Dynasty. * Ibn Muqlah, Islamic calligrapher, is disgraced and imprisoned in Baghdad. * Pope Leo VII succeeds Pope John XI as the 126th pope. == Births == * Abu al-Qasim al-Zahrawi, Moorish scholar * Li Houzhu, last Chinese emperor of the Southern Tang == Deaths == * Henry I the Fowler, King of the Germans * Gyeonhwon, King of Hubaekje
